The Hamiltonian matrix $H$ is a Hermitian matrix , which satisfies ${H^ * } = H$ , so that $U$ is a unitary matrix , which satisfies
\begin{equation}
{U^ * } \cdot U = I
\end{equation}
The property is the key to guarantee that the state $\psi \left( t \right)$ keeps a unit length .
